LAGOS – President of the Association of Advertising Agencies of Nigeria (AAAN) Mr. Nkechi Odigbo has challenged advertising practitioners and agencies on the African continent to begin to drive growth and economic development of the continent. Odigbo,who gave the challenge during his remarks at the Lagos Advertising and Ideas Festival (LAIF) awards Masterclass session on Wednesday in Lagos, said it is high time for Nigerian advertising practitioners to channel their creative energy towards more strategic global societal pursuits, noting that they must look beyond just winning market shares or making profit to becoming springboard for driving innovation and improving the overall quality of life on the continent. He added: “We cannot solely depend on the western nation; we cannot also afford to wait for our governments to start seeing beyond the symptom to begin to attend to the larger affairs of nation building.”